One algorithm for sorting a list of numbers from low to high would be a Bubble Sort. Bubble Sort is a simple algorithm for sorting a list of numbers. The algorithm repeatedly steps through the list, comparing adjacent elements and swapping them if they are in the wrong order. The algorithm continues until it passes through the whole list without needing to swap any elements. It can be written as a program in any programming language.

def bubbleSort(list): 
    n = len(list) 

    # Traverse through all array elements 
    for i in range(n): 

        # Last i elements are already in place 
        for j in range(0, n-i-1): 

            # traverse the array from 0 to n-i-1 
            # Swap if the element found is greater 
            # than the next element 
            if list[j] > list[j+1] : 
                list[j], list[j+1] = list[j+1], list[j] 

    return list

